 Agree to provide all information to NRCS determined to be necessary
to assess the merits of a proposed project and to monitor cost-share
agreement compliance;

 Agree to grant to NRCS or its representatives access to the land
for purposes related to application, assessment, monitoring,
enforcement, verification of certifications, or other actions
required to implement this part;

 With onsite or offsite conditions which NRCS determines would
undermine the benefits of the habitat development or otherwise
reduce its value;

 Contribution to resolving an identified habitat concern of
national, tribal, regional, or State importance including at-risk
species;

 The parties to the cost-share agreement are unable to comply with
the terms of the cost-share agreement as the result of conditions
beyond their control;
